  "text": "In epithelial cells, VacA is known to disrupt vesicular trafficking due to formation of anion-selective channels in the membranes of late endocytic compartments [CITATION_1] . We therefore sought to determine whether a similar mechanism is employed in mac- rophages and whether phagosomal processing of L. acidophilus is necessary for the induction of IFN-␤. BMDMs were preincubated for 30 min with the endosomal acidification blockers chloroquine and bafilomycin A1 prior to stimulation with L. acidophilus (Fig. 3D) . Viability of the cells was verified via trypan blue staining (data not shown). Both inhibitors completely blocked the release of IFN-␤, indicating that phagosomal maturation and processing of L. acidophilus are required for the production of IFN-␤ (*, P Ͻ 0.01).",
